# Web Development Workflow

Before writing or editing React/Next.js code in `apps/web` (or any future web app under `apps/`), **read and apply** the skills and rules below.

## Design doc first (if present)

If `DESIGN.md` exists at the repo root or `apps/web/DESIGN.md`, **read it before any UI or CSS work**. It overrides generic skill guidance for colors, typography, spacing, and component patterns. See `.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc`.

## Always apply

| Source | Path | Use for |
|--------|------|---------|
| Design system | `.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc` | `DESIGN.md` lookup, tokens, component conventions |
| Code quality | `.cursor/rules/code-quality.mdc` | Modularity, file size, DRY, control flow |
| Web structure | `.cursor/rules/web-structure.mdc` | App Router layout, components, RSC boundaries |

## Read these skills first

| Skill | Path | Use for |
|-------|------|---------|
| React best practices | `.agents/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/SKILL.md` | Performance, data fetching, bundle size, rerenders |
| Next.js best practices | `.agents/skills/next-best-practices/SKILL.md` | File conventions, RSC, async APIs, metadata, errors |
| Frontend design | `.agents/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md` | New UI, visual direction, typography, layout |
| Web design guidelines | `.agents/skills/web-design-guidelines/SKILL.md` | Accessibility, UX audits, Vercel interface compliance |
| Tailwind v4 docs | `.agents/skills/tailwind-4-docs/SKILL.md` | Utilities, `@theme`, variants, migration gotchas |

## When to use each skill

- **Building or changing UI** → `DESIGN.md` (if present) → frontend-design + vercel-react-best-practices + next-best-practices
- **Styling with Tailwind** → `DESIGN.md` tokens (if present) → tailwind-4-docs (check docs snapshot; use `references/engineering-playbook.md` if not initialized)
- **Reviewing UI/UX or accessibility** → web-design-guidelines (fetch latest guidelines per skill)
- **Any web code change** → code-quality + web-structure

## Agent checklist

1. If `DESIGN.md` exists, read it before skills or implementation.
2. Read relevant skill files before implementing — do not rely on memory alone.
3. Follow `code-quality.mdc` limits; split files/components before they grow.
4. Prefer Server Components; add `'use client'` only when required.
5. Compose Tailwind utilities in markup; use `:root` tokens and `@theme` per `DESIGN.md` and tailwind-4-docs.
6. Run `pnpm exec turbo lint check-types --filter=web` after changes.
